heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 16.2mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 4th in our overall records.  The storm lasted 5.3 hours and 9.2mm of rain fell.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.0mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: A relentless rainstorm took place on 04 January 2025, it lasted 37.2 hours and it delivered 36.8mm of rain at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 3.5°C), outside temperature (down 3.2°C), and inside temperature (down 2.0°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%) and rainfall (up 0.1 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 635 m), rainfall (down 0.1 mm), and light levels (up 4678 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1233 m), light levels (up 6641 lux), and rainfall (down 0.6 mm) when compared to today.
